- content_for :title, "Good Issues - Coming Soon"

.card
  .card-header
    %h4.mb-0
      %i.bi.bi-lightbulb.me-2
      Good Issues Framework
  .card-body
    .row
      .col-md-8
        %h5 What are Good Issues?
        %p Good issues are specific, relevant, and solvable problems that teams can effectively discuss and resolve. They prevent teams from spinning their wheels on unfocused conversations.
        
        %h6.mt-4 Key Features Coming:
        %ul
          %li
            %strong Specific: 
            %span.text-muted Start with no-judgement observations, personal-unmet-needs, and a proposal of a goal that would benefit the group
          %li
            %strong Relevant: 
            %span.text-muted Must be traceable to Mission, Vision, and/or Values; not to mention the Big 7 or some strategic objective
          %li
            %strong Solvable: 
            %span.text-muted Must have more than one possible solution, ensuring we're making change not pushing one solution forward
          %li
            %strong Decider Presence: 
            %span.text-muted The person who should be the decider must be in the room
        
        %h6.mt-4 Vision:
        %p This system will ensure all team discussions are focused on truly solvable problems with clear ownership and appropriate decision-making authority.
        
      .col-md-4
        .card.bg-light
          .card-body
            %h6.text-primary
              %i.bi.bi-target.me-2
              Focused Discussions
            %p.small Good issues prevent teams from spinning their wheels on unfocused conversations.
            
            %hr
            
            %h6.text-success
              %i.bi.bi-check-circle.me-2
              Decision Ready
            %ul.small
              %li Clear ownership
              %li Appropriate decider present
              %li Multiple solutions available
              %li Strategic alignment
